When you run the below rest call, it will include all sprint which consist of *closed/deleted* sprint as well.

*Rest query*
{code}
http://localhost:8313/rest/greenhopper/1.0/sprintquery/3?include=FutureSprint=true&includeHistoricSprints=true&maxResults=2000
{code}
(i) Replace the {{http://localhost:8313}} and {{rapidViewId}} to the corresponding value.

*Result*
{code}
{
    "sprints": [
        {
            "id": 2,
            "sequence": 2,
            "name": "Sprint 1",
            "state": "CLOSED",
            "linkedPagesCount": 0
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "sequence": 3,
            "name": "Sprint 2",
            "state": "CLOSED",
            "linkedPagesCount": 0
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "sequence": 4,
            "name": "Sprint 3",
            "state": "ACTIVE",
            "linkedPagesCount": 0
        }
    ],
    "rapidViewId": 3
}
{code}

*Suggestion*
It would be better if we can filter out the closed/deleted sprint and only list out the active sprint.

